Simple Ising Model Simulations

Program files

    ising_simple.cc : source code
    ising_simple_j1 : executable
    ising_test.sh : test script using values described below
    Makefile : program makefile
    README : this document

Output files

    *** N = # of spins, M = # of sweeps, B = Beta
    *** J = J_{ij} seed, MC = spins and MC sweep seed 

    *** All J values are +1 except 0 main diagonal ***
    *** FERRO command line argument = 0 ***
    ising_output1.csv : N = 4, M = 100, B = 0.1, J = 3, MC = 5
    ising_output2.csv : N = 4, M = 100, B = 1, J = 3, MC = 6
    ising_output3.csv : N = 4, M = 100, B = 10, J = 3, MC = 7
    ising_output4.csv : N = 16, M = 100, B = 0.1, J = 4, MC = 8
    ising_output5.csv : N = 16, M = 100, B = 1, J = 4, MC = 9
    ising_output6.csv : N = 16, M = 100, B = 10, J = 4, MC = 10
    ising_output7.csv : N = 64, M = 100, B = 0.1, J = 5, MC = 11
    ising_output8.csv : N = 64, M = 100, B = 1, J = 5, MC = 12
    ising_output9.csv : N = 64, M = 100, B = 10, J = 5, MC = 13

    *** Random J values except 0 main diagonal *** 
    *** FERRO command line argument = 1 ***
    ising_output10.csv : N = 8, M = 100, B = 0.1, J = 6, MC = 14
    ising_output11.csv : N = 8, M = 100, B = 1, J = 6, MC = 15
    ising_output12.csv : N = 8, M = 100, B = 10, J = 6, MC = 16
    ising_output13.csv : N = 16, M = 100, B = 0.1, J = 7, MC = 17
    ising_output14.csv : N = 16, M = 100, B = 1, J = 7, MC = 18
    ising_output15.csv : N = 16, M = 100, B = 10, J = 7, MC = 19
    ising_output16.csv : N = 32, M = 100, B = 0.1, J = 8, MC = 20
    ising_output17.csv : N = 32, M = 100, B = 1, J = 8, MC = 21
    ising_output18.csv : N = 32, M = 100, B = 10, J = 8, MC = 22

Analysis files

    ising_analysis.nb : Mathematica notebook with energy equilibration plots
